  "prompt": "What is the best thing to do if I have feelings for another girl when I am already in a 3 years relationship?",
  "response": "If you're experiencing feelings for someone else while in a committed relationship, here are some recommended steps:\n\n1. Self-reflection\n- Analyze why these feelings have developed\n- Understand the root cause of your attraction\n- Determine if there are underlying issues in your current relationship\n\n2. Maintain boundaries\n- Limit contact with the person you're attracted to\n- Avoid putting yourself in situations that could lead to temptation\n- Be honest with yourself about potential risks\n\n3. Communicate with your partner\n- Be open and honest about your feelings\n- Discuss any relationship concerns or issues\n- Work together to address potential problems\n\n4. Consider relationship counseling\n- A professional can help navigate complex emotions\n- Provide guidance on relationship dynamics\n- Help improve communication\n\n5. Make a clear decision\n- Choose to recommit to your current relationship\n- Work on strengthening your connection\n- Or consider ending the relationship if you feel incompatible\n\n6. Prioritize integrity\n- Act with respect for your partner\n- Avoid emotional or physical infidelity\n- Make ethical choices\n\n7. If needed, consider ending the relationship\n- If you genuinely have stronger feelings for someone else\n- If you cannot recommit to your current partner\n\nRemember, feelings are complex. The most important things are honesty, respect, and making decisions that maintain your personal integrity.",
